Translation:
We have detected that you have disabled "cookie" support for this website. You can do that, but please be aware that, without cookies to track your anonymous identity, you will not be able to resume a partially-filled form should your session be interrupted for some reason.

Also, do not copy the URL you are using to fill out this survey and share it with anybody else. If you do, they can see and resume your session.
Context: The warning message that appears when a user has disabled cookies.

Translation: You have already started filling out this form and last updated it on {0}. Resume from where you left off, or discard that version and start again? (If you choose to start again, the old version will be discarded and there is no undo.)
Context: This is the message in the 'resume form' pop-up that is presented when a logged-in user returns after their session expires. {0} gets replaced with the date and time of the last form session and must be included in your translation.

Translation: You are about to start a new form for case ID "{0}". We noticed that you haven't finished filling out the form for case ID "{1}". Do you want to resume filling out that form, or start a new one?
Context: Whenever a user visits a form that they had already started filling out, SurveyCTO attempts to resume the partially-filled form from memory. If the partially-filled form has a dfferent case ID than the current URL, a pop-up will appear with this message asking which form they wish to fill out. {0} will be replaced by the case ID from the current URL, and {1} will be replaced by the case ID from memory. Both {0} and {1} must be included in your translation.
The button label to continue filling out the partially-filled form from memory. {0} will be replaced by the case ID from memory and must be included in your translation.
The button label to start a brand new form with a new case iD. {0} will be replaced by the case ID from the current URL and must be included in your translation.
The title of the pop-up message prompting which case ID to use.
This is the button label to discard changes in the pop-up when you attempt to start over.
